						               													<description>In the Gelato game we love to eat ice cream and our goal is to be the first player to get 3 ice cream cards.&amp;#10;Gelato is a game of strategy and opportunity in which we must know how to manage the result of the dice roll to achieve victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OBJECTIVE&amp;#10;Be the first to get 3 ice cream cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SETUP&amp;#10;Place the 11 ice cream cards on the table, distribute each player 3 tiles of the same color and leave the 3 dice on the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO PLAY:&amp;#10;The youngest player starts. You must roll all 3 dice and be left with only the result of 2 dice (the other discards it).&amp;#10;You must add them and with that result you can take an action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With the value of the sum of 2 dice you have 3 options:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Draw a token from your reserve and place it in the first position on the card of that value.&amp;#10;- Advance a token already placed on a card of that value.&amp;#10;- Remove one of his tokens from one of the cards he previously placed and relocate it to position 1 of the card of that value.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO DRAW A LETTER:&amp;#10;When a player reaches the final position of a card, he takes it for himself. He places it in front of him turned and leaves the used token on it being unused. He will play with one less chip.&amp;#10;If other players 'tokens are found on the card to be lifted, they return to their owners' reserve.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAME OVER:&amp;#10;The first player to get 3 cards in their possession wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;ADVANCED VERSION&amp;#10;It is played the same as the base game but the 4 effect cards are mixed, the first 2 are taken and placed on the table. The remaining 2 are removed from the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These letters have actions. Some are executed immediately and others on the next turn of whoever chose it. A player achieves an effect when one of his pieces is placed in the middle position of a card with its numerical value in white.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At that time you can select one of the 2 visible effects. Then that card must turn it over and the effect of its reverse will be the one that can be chosen in the future.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
